File: A City of Tshwane Health official looks on as she conducts a screening exercise on a taxi operator before testing for the COVID-19 coronavirus at the Bloed Street Mall in Pretoria Central Business District. JOHANNESBURG - COVID-19 cases in South Africa continue to surge as just over 6,000 new infections have been recorded. The total number of infections in SA is at 144, 264. The Health Department says 73 new deaths have been recorded. IN NUMBERS: COVID-19 in SA Most of the new deaths come from the Western Cape. This takes the national death toll to 2529. Nearly 1.6 million coronavirus tests have been conducted. South Africa has seen over 70,000 recoveries. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs. Health Media Release 29 June 2020 v1 by Travis Richards on Scribd  #COVID19 statistics in SA as at 29 June 2020. pic.twitter.com/FgnK8UZBJU